                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.11/40.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Unalga</hi> will remain available at Port Said at least until
                    arrival of a cruiser at Beirut.</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
